OL,3,CVoters can judge me in 2031 if I miss
OL,4,Cchild poverty target ` Swinney
OL,6,FJohn Swinney has said voters will be
OL,7,Fable to judge him in 2031 if he misses
OL,8,Fthe Government's child poverty target,
OL,9,Fas he hinted he will not resign if he
OL,10,Ffails to achieve his key pledge.
OL,12,FSince taking office in 2024, the First
OL,13,FMinister has made the eradication of
OL,14,Fchild poverty his driving mission, but
OL,15,Fthe Government remains well short of
OL,16,Freducing the rate ` which currently
OL,17,Fsits at 22% ` to 10% by the end of the
OL,18,Fdecade.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G1/7
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,304,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30302
SC,0002
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F303A1773288217
OL,3,CVoters can judge me in 2031 if I miss
OL,4,Cchild poverty target ` Swinney
OL,6,FThe Government has already missed its
OL,7,Finterim target of reducing the rate to
OL,8,F18% by 2023-24.
OL,10,FWith the SNP still enjoying a
OL,11,Fsubstantial lead over opposition
OL,12,Fparties in the polls and Mr Swinney
OL,13,Flooking to be in power after May's
OL,14,Felection, he refused to say when asked
OL,15,Fby the Press Association if he will
OL,16,Fresign if he misses the goal.
OL,18,F"I'm just going to do everything I can
OL,19,Fto make sure we achieve those targets
OL,20,Fand make the priorities within
OL,21,FGovernment to do all of that," he said.
OL,26,@zD@AOU}D@^O]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G2/7
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,304,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30303
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F303A1773288217
OL,3,CVoters can judge me in 2031 if I miss
OL,4,Cchild poverty target ` Swinney
OL,6,F"Those are the substantial commitments
OL,7,FI make to the public in Scotland to
OL,8,Fmake sure that we put the resources in
OL,9,Fplace to support the policies that can
OL,10,Fachieve that objective.
OL,12,F"Now, of course, I'm doing that within
OL,13,Fa context of prevailing conditions in
OL,14,Fthe UK that could be very hostile to
OL,15,Fthe agenda that I'm taking forward.
OL,17,F"I will do my level best to achieve
OL,18,Fthat and allow the people of Scotland
OL,19,Fto judge on my record."
OL,26,@nD@AOUtD@AOUyD@AOU{D@WO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G3/7
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,304,300,200,140,000,100
